<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>4327</id>
    <title>Apostrophe displayed incorrectly when replying from a notification</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">### Expected behavior</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">When replying to a comment notification, if you leave the same comment twice, a message pops up that should say "_Duplicate comment detected; It looks as through you've already said that!</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">_"</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">### Actual behavior
The message doesn't render the apostrophe correctly, and actually reads as "_Duplicate comment detected; It looks as through you#8217;ve already said that!</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">_</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">This only happens when replying from the notification.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">Replying from the Reader displays a more basic "_Couldn't post your comment_" popup.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">!</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">### Steps to reproduce the behavior</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">1 Open the app and tap the notifications icon</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.3">2 Scroll down to a comment notification, and open it</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.4">3 Use the 'Reply to [Commenter Name] field to submit a comment</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.5">4 Once the comment is submitted, try saying the same thing again to trigger the popup</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">##### Tested on HTC One M9, Android 6.0</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
